    "#### Simple QPE circuit with a phase gate\n",

   "id": "equivalent-customer",

   "source": [

   "outputs": [

     "output_type": "execute_result"

   ],
   "source": [
    "# simple qpe circuit with a phase gate\n",
    "phase0 = np.pi/4\n",
    "n_prec0 = 3\n",
    "\n",
    "qpe_simple = QuantumCircuit(n_prec0+1, n_prec0)\n",
    "qpe_simple.h(range(n_prec0))\n",
    "qpe_simple.x(n_prec0)\n",
    "for k in range(n_prec0):\n",
    "    qpe_simple.cp(phase0*2**k, k, n_prec0)\n",
    "qpe_simple.append(QFT(n_prec0).inverse(), range(n_prec0))\n",
    "qpe_simple.measure(range(n_prec0), range(n_prec0))\n",
    "\n",
    "qpe_simple.draw('mpl')"
   ]

   "source": [

    "\n",
    "- 'initialize' method\n",

   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "from qiskit.quantum_info import random_unitary\n",
    "import numpy.linalg as la"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cellular-thunder",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "[quantum_info module](https://qiskit.org/documentation/apidoc/quantum_info.html#module-qiskit.quantum_info)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "tired-radical",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "phase to estimate: 2.704\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Phase to estimate\n",
    "n_st = 2\n",
    "Urand = random_unitary(2**n_st)\n",
    "vals, vecs = la.eig(Urand)\n",
    "val, st = vals[1], vecs[:, 1]\n",
    "if np.angle(val) < 0:\n",
    "    phase = 2*np.pi + np.angle(val)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    phase = np.angle(val)\n",
    "    \n",
    "print('phase to estimate: {}'.format(np.round(phase, 3)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "primary-soldier",
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true

   "outputs": [

     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# circuit for eigenstate prep\n",
    "qc_st = QuantumCircuit(n_st)\n",
    "qc_st.initialize(st)\n",
    "qc_st.draw('mpl')"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "distinguished-manchester",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "n_prec = 6\n",
    "U = Urand.to_instruction()\n",
    "\n",
    "qpe = QuantumCircuit(n_prec+n_st, n_prec)\n",
    "qpe.h(range(n_prec))\n",
    "qpe.append(qc_st, [-2, -1])\n",
    "\n",
    "for k in range(n_prec):\n",
    "    qpe.append(U.power(2**k).control(), [k, -2, -1])\n",
    "\n",
    "qpe.append(QFT(n_prec).inverse(), range(n_prec))\n",
    "qpe.measure(range(n_prec), range(n_prec))\n",
    "qpe.draw('mpl')"
   ]

    "### AerSimulator \n",
    "\n",
    "- `qiskit_aer` is a qiskit simulation package.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "- `AerSimulator` simulates experiments and returns counts.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "- By default, `AerSimulator` execute `shots=1024` realizations of a circuit under ideal condition.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "- A specific simulator or device is called a `backend`.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "- `backend.run` takes a quantum circuit, or list of circuits, and execute the circuits on the chosen backend."
   ]
